{"action": "input", "code": "def main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    color, color_number = count_colored_grids(input_grid)\n    scale_number = calculate_scale_number(input_grid, color_number)\n    output = scale_and_copy_grid(input_grid, color_number, scale_number)\n    return output\ndef scale_and_copy(input_grid: np.ndarray, color_number: int, scale_number: int) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Scales the input grid and copies it to the output grid.\n\n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid.\n    color_number: An integer representing the number of colored grids in the input.\n    scale_number: An integer representing the scale number.\n\n    Returns:\n    A numpy array representing the output grid.\n    \"\"\"\n    output = np.zeros((input_grid.shape[0] * scale_number, input_grid.shape[1] * scale_number))\n    output[:input_grid.shape[0], :input_grid.shape[1]] = input_grid\n    for i in range(1, color_number):\n        output[:input_grid.shape[0], i * input_grid.shape[1]:(i + 1) * input_grid.shape[1]] = input_grid\n    for i in range(1, scale_number):\n        output[i * input_grid.shape[0]:(i + 1) * input_grid.shape[0], :] = output[:input_grid.shape[0], :]\n    return output\ndef calculate_scale_number(input_grid: np.ndarray, color_number: int) -> int:\n    \"\"\"\n    Calculates the scale number based on the input grid's width and color number.\n\n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid.\n    color_number: An integer representing the number of colored grids in the input.\n\n    Returns:\n    An integer representing the scale number.\n    \"\"\"\n    return input_grid.shape[1] - color_number\ndef count_colored_grids(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> Tuple[int, int]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Counts the number of colored grids in the input and returns the color and the color_number.\n\n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid.\n\n    Returns:\n    A tuple containing the color and the color_number.\n    \"\"\"\n    color, color_number = np.unique(input_grid, return_counts=True)\n    color_number = color_number[1] if len(color) > 1 and color[0] == 0 else color_number[0]\n    color = color[1] if len(color) > 1 and color[0] == 0 else color[0]\n    return (color, color_number)\ndef scale_and_copy_grid(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Counts the number of colored grids in the input, calculates the scale number, and scales and copies the input grid to the output grid.\n\n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid.\n\n    Returns:\n    A numpy array representing the output grid.\n    \"\"\"\n    color, color_number = count_colored_grids(input_grid)\n    scale_number = calculate_scale_number(input_grid, color_number)\n    output = scale_and_copy(input_grid, color_number, scale_number)\n    return output", "user_code": "def main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    color, color_number = `count the number of colored grids in the input, and return the color and the color_number`(input_grid)\n    scale_number = `scale_number equals input_grid's width minus color_number`(input_grid, color_number)\n    output = `the output dimensions are scaled by the scale_number compared to the input_grid, both in width and height.initiate the output to be whole black. start from the left top, copy the input_grid to the left top of the output. Copy from left to right, then from top to down, until copied the input color_number times. return output`(input_grid, color_number, scale_number)\n    return output", "gpt_code": "def scale_and_copy(input_grid: np.ndarray, color_number: int, scale_number: int) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Scales the input grid and copies it to the output grid.\n\n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid.\n    color_number: An integer representing the number of colored grids in the input.\n    scale_number: An integer representing the scale number.\n\n    Returns:\n