{"action": "edit", "code": "def replicate_pattern(input_grid: np.ndarray, color_number: int, scale_number: int) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Replicates the pattern from the input grid to the output grid.\n\n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid.\n    color_number: An integer representing the number of colored grids in the input.\n    scale_number: An integer representing the scale number.\n\n    Returns:\n    A numpy array representing the output grid.\n    \"\"\"\n    output_width = input_grid.shape[1] * scale_number\n    output_height = input_grid.shape[0] * scale_number\n    output = np.full((output_height, output_width), black)\n    for i in range(color_number):\n        start_col = i * input_grid.shape[1]\n        end_col = start_col + input_grid.shape[1]\n        output[:, start_col:end_col] = np.where(input_grid == i + 1, i + 1, black)\n    return output\ndef main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    color, color_number = count_colored_grids(input_grid)\n    scale_number = calculate_scale_number(input_grid, color_number)\n    output = replicate_pattern_main(input_grid, color_number, scale_number)\n    return output\ndef replicate_pattern_main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Replicates the pattern from the input grid to the output grid.\n\n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid.\n\n    Returns:\n    A numpy array representing the output grid.\n    \"\"\"\n    color, color_number = count_colored_grids(input_grid)\n    scale_number = calculate_scale_number(input_grid, color_number)\n    output = replicate_pattern(input_grid, color_number, scale_number)\n    return output\ndef calculate_scale_number(input_grid: np.ndarray, color_number: int) -> int:\n    \"\"\"\n    Calculates the scale number based on the input grid's width and color number.\n\n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid.\n    color_number: An integer representing the number of colored grids in the input.\n\n    Returns:\n    An integer representing the scale number.\n    \"\"\"\n    return input_grid.shape[1] - color_number\ndef count_colored_grids(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> Tuple[int, int]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Counts the number of colored grids in the input and returns the color and the color_number.\n\n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid.\n\n    Returns:\n    A tuple containing the color and the color_number.\n    \"\"\"\n    color, color_number = np.unique(input_grid, return_counts=True)\n    color_number = color_number[1] if len(color) > 1 and color[0] == 0 else color_number[0]\n    color = color[1] if len(color) > 1 and color[0] == 0 else color[0]\n    return (color, color_number)", "user_code": "\ndef main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    color, color_number = `count the number of colored grids in the input, and return the color and the color_number`(input_grid)\n    scale_number = `scale_number equals input_grid's width minus color_number`(input_grid, color_number)\n    output = `the output dimensions are scaled by the scale_number compared to the input_grid, both in width and height.initiate the output to be whole black. copy the exact pattern from the input grid to the output grid, with the same number of times as the color_number starting from the left side to the right. For example, if the pattern on the input grid has 3 colored grids, you will copy the exact pattern to the output grid 3 times, starting from the left to the right; if the pattern on the input grid has 5 colored grids, you will copy the exact pattern to the output grid 5 times, starting from the left to the right.`(input_grid, color_number, scale_number)\n    return output", "gpt_code": "def replicate_pattern(input_grid: np.ndarray, color_number: int, scale_number: int) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Replicates the pattern from the input grid to the output grid.\n\n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid.\n    color_number: An integer representing the number of colored grids in the input.\n    scale_number: An integer representing the scale number.\n\n    Returns:\n    A numpy array representing the output grid.\n    \"\"\"\n    output_width = input_grid.shape[1] * scale_number\n    output_height = input_grid.shape[0] * scale_number\n    output = np.full((output_height, output_width), black)\n    for i in range(color_number):\n        start_col = i * input_grid.shape[1]\n        end_col = start_col + input_grid.shape[1]\n        output[:, start_col:end_col] = np.where(input_grid == i + 1, i + 1, black)\n    return output\ndef replicate_pattern_main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Replicates the pattern from the input grid to the output grid.\n\n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid.\n\n    Returns:\n    A numpy array representing the output grid.\n    \"\"\"\n    color, color_number = count_colored_grids(input_grid)\n    scale_number = calculate_scale_number(input_grid, color_number)\n    output = replicate_pattern(input_grid, color_number, scale_number)\n    return output\ndef calculate_scale_number(input_grid: np.ndarray, color_number: int) -> int:\n    \"\"\"\n    Calculates the scale number based on the input grid's width and color number.\n\n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid.\n    color_number: An integer representing the number of colored grids in the input.\n\n    Returns:\n    An integer representing the scale number.\n    \"\"\"\n    return input_grid.shape[1] - color_number\ndef count_colored_grids(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> Tuple[int, int]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Counts the number of colored grids in the input and returns the color and the color_number.\n\n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid.\n\n    Returns:\n    A tuple containing the color and the color_number.\n    \"\"\"\n    color, color_number = np.unique(input_grid, retu